OL,3,CWRU say 'don't gamble with Welsh
OL,4,CRugby's future' as they issue 'stark
OL,5,Cwarning'
OL,7,FThe WRU says the proposed motions
OL,8,Fwould "reverse hard-won progress,
OL,9,Fstall vital investment, and jeopardise
OL,10,Fthe prosperity of Welsh rugby at every
OL,11,Flevel."
OL,13,FThey insist a #28 million investment
OL,14,Fin pathways, academies, coaching,
OL,15,Ftalent and insights, and Super Rygbi
OL,16,FCymru is at stake, along with
OL,17,Ffinancial and commercial stability.
